17. Repo-ready summary block

Living Word Dynamics v1.0

Words are not static dictionary objects but continuity-patterns that persist through semantic turnover. A word maintains identity by preserving a continuity kernel while metabolizing context, function, affect, and social use over time. This makes words structurally similar to Ship-of-Theseus systems: recognizable despite replacement of parts. Meaning should therefore be modeled as trajectory, not fixed state; translation should preserve invariant mapping, not merely token form; and many communication failures are best understood as resolution mismatch rather than disagreement.

